---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const headshot = '/megan-barker.webp';
const headshotExists = true;
---

<Layout title="About" description="Security engineer and technical writer based in Ontario, Canada.">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="bg-slate-900 text-white border-b border-slate-800">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">The arc</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">
        Security engineer and technical writer based in Ontario, Canada.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">

    <!-- Two-column layout: photo left, text right (stacks on mobile) -->
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-16 items-start">

      <!-- Photo column -->
      <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-28">
        {headshotExists ? (
          <img
            src={headshot}
            alt="Megan Barker"
            class="w-full max-w-xs mx-auto lg:mx-0 rounded-2xl shadow-lg grayscale"
          />
        ) : (
          <!-- Placeholder shown until you drop the image in -->
          <div class="w-full max-w-xs mx-auto lg:mx-0 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-200 to-amber-100 aspect-[3/4] flex items-center justify-center">
            <p class="font-mono text-sm text-slate-400 text-center px-4">
              drop megan-barker.webp<br />into /public/
            </p>
          </div>
        )}

        <!-- Contact links -->
        <div class="mt-6 max-w-xs mx-auto lg:mx-0 flex flex-col gap-2">
          <a
            href="mailto:&#109;&#101;&#64;&#109;&#101;&#103;&#97;&#110;&#98;&#97;&#114;&#107;&#101;&#114;&#46;&#99;&#97;"
            class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors"
          >
            Email
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://linkedin.com/in/megan-writes/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors"
          >
            LinkedIn
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text column -->
      <div>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">

          <p>
            I've been a writer (nearly) my entire life. I was the kid who read the dictionary and thesaurus for fun and wrote chaptered novels
            when a short story was the assignment. Eventually my love of words shaped my career as a Security Specialist because documentation wasn't a maligned side task, it was my bread and butter.
          </p>

          <p>
            For years, I translated deeply technical concepts into clear prose: passkeys, zero-knowledge architecture,
            the principle of least privilege, quantum threats to modern authentication. I became very good at making
            difficult concepts accessible.
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-800 font-medium text-xl">
            Then I was promoted to Security Engineer.
          </p>

          <p>
            Now I'm building the systems I used to
            explain. I write R, Markdown, and Go. I'm designing CI/CD pipelines and deploying on AWS. I think about
            authentication flows not just as a writer documenting them, but as an engineer responsible for them.
          </p>

          <p>
            I live in Ontario, Canada with my son and our rescued bully, Sky.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-slate-100 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/engineering" class="bg-slate-900 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-slate-700 transition-colors">
            See what I build
          </a>
          <a href="/writing" class="border border-slate-200 text-slate-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:border-slate-400 hover:text-slate-900 transition-colors">
            Read what I write
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
